Sentence: Bacterial toxin B ( inactivates RhoA, B, and C; CDC42; Rac proteins), C3 ADP - ribosyltransferase ( C3) toxin from C. botulinum ( inactivates RhoA, B, and C proteins), and Y - 27632 ( selective inhibitor of Rho - associated kinases) increased the LPS / IFN - gamma - mediated iNOS expression.
